    class Node {
        constructor(a, b) {
            this.x = a;
            this.y = b;
        }

        toString() {
            return "(" + this.x.toFixed(2) + ", " + this.y.toFixed(2) + ")";
        }
    }
    class Edge {
        constructor(node_a, node_b) {
            this.node_1 = node_a;
            this.node_2 = node_b;
        }
        toString() {
            return "[" + this.node_1.toString() + ", " + this.node_2.toString() + "]";
        }
    }
    class Tree {
        constructor(gens, lineLength, x, y, angle, rotation) {
            let xangle = cycle_in_range(angle,0,2160) 
            <!-- [A % 2160-->
            <!--  current_angle = ((angle + 90) % 360)/2/3-->
            current_angle = ((xangle + 90)/6)-60;
            <!--  if (current_angle < 0) {-->
            <!--      current_angle = current_angle + 360;-->
            <!--  }-->

            <!--  lineLength = (360 - current_angle )/12;-->
            <!--  lineLength = Math.min(lineLength, maxlength)-->
            <!--  console.log("-----------------------------",lineLength)-->

            <!--  current_gen = gens-->
            <!--  all trees have a base node -->

            <!--  lineLength = randint(lineLength,lineLength+(current_x/1000))-->
            <!--  lineLength = randint(lineLength,Math.floor(lineLength*(vx/200)))-->
            <!--  lineLength = lineLength*(1/vx)-->

            this.base_node = new Node(x, y);
            <!--  check if we are at end of tree -->


            <!--  lineLength = maxlength-->
            <!--  let today = new Date(), today_abs = new Date(), today_secs = 0;-->
            <!--  today_abs.setHours(0);-->
            <!--  today_abs.setMinutes(0);-->
            <!--  today_abs.setSeconds(0);-->
            <!--  today_secs = ((today.getTime() - today_abs.getTime()) / 1000) - 14400;-->
            <!--  color_sec = cycle_in_range(today_secs % 360,0, 256)-->

            if (gens > 0) {
                let Rangle = 0;
                let Langle = 0;

                if (freehand === 0) {
                    Rangle = angle;
                    Langle = angle;
                }
                <!--  creates interactive offset-->
                if (freehand === 1) {
                    Rangle = angle * (current_x / 300);
                    Langle = angle * (current_x / 300);
                }
                <!--  creates interactive offset-->
                if (freehand === 2) {
                    Rangle = angle; 
                    <!-- (current_y/1000)-->
                    Langle = angle;
                     <!-- (current_y/1000)-->
                }

                if (freehand === 3) {
                    Rangle = angle - (90);
                    Langle = angle * (current_x / 1000);
                }

                if (freehand === 4) {
                    Rangle = angle + (1 * current_level);
                    <!-- * (current_y/1000)-->
                    Langle = angle + Rangle;
                    <!-- * (current_x/1000)-->
                }

                this.xcR = Math.cos(toRadians(Rangle - rotation))
                this.ycR = Math.sin(toRadians(Rangle - rotation))
                this.xcL = Math.cos(toRadians(Langle + rotation))
                this.ycL = Math.sin(toRadians(Langle + rotation))
                <!--  determine next node to the right in the tree with trig -->
                this.right_node = new Node(
                    x + lineLength * this.xcR,
                    y + lineLength * this.ycR
                );

                <!--  tline( x, y, this.xcR, this.ycR, tlevel, angle,length)-->
                <!--  tline( x, y, this.xcL, this.ycL, tlevel, angle,length)-->

                <!--  determine next node to the left in the tree with trig -->
                this.left_node = new Node(
                    x + lineLength * this.xcL,
                    y + lineLength * this.ycL
                );

                <!--  create edges in the graph that connect the base node to the following nodes -->
                this.right_branch = new Edge(this.base_node, this.right_node);
                this.left_branch = new Edge(this.base_node, this.left_node);

                <!--  generate a tree beginning at the left node, with a lower depth and new start angle -->
                this.left_tree = new Tree(
                    gens - 1,
                    lineLength,
                    this.left_node.x,
                    this.left_node.y,
                    angle + rotation,
                    rotation
                );


                <!--  generate a tree beginning at the right node, with a lower depth and new start angle -->
                this.right_tree = new Tree(
                    gens - 1,
                    lineLength,
                    this.right_node.x,
                    this.right_node.y,
                    angle - rotation,
                    rotation
                );


                current_xlen = this.left_node.x
                current_ylen = this.left_node.y

                prev_ylen = current_ylen
                current_xrange = Math.max(Math.abs(current_xlen),current_xrange)
                current_yrange = Math.max(Math.abs(current_ylen),current_yrange)
                <!--  console.log(current_yrange,current_ylimit)-->
                setYinRange()
                tline( x, y, this.left_node.x,  this.left_node.y,  current_level, angle,lineLength);
                tline( x, y, this.right_node.x, this.right_node.y, current_level, angle,lineLength);
                <!--  tline( x, y, this.left_node.x, this.left_node.y, tlevel, angle,lineLength)-->
                <!--  tline( x, y, this.right_node.x, this.right_node.y, tlevel, angle,lineLength)-->

            }
        }
    }
    function getTreeEdges(tree) {
        tlevel++
        <!--  cOrder.push(tlevel)-->
        if (tree.left_tree) {
            var edges = getTreeEdges(tree.right_tree).concat(getTreeEdges(tree.left_tree));
            edges.push(tree.left_branch);
            edgeNum++
            edges.push(tree.right_branch);
            edgeNum++
            return edges;
        } else {
            return [];
        }
        tlevel--

    }

    function drawLine(args) {
        let line = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'line');
        line.id = args['idname'];

        let strokeWidth = args['width']
        if (SHOWLINES > 0) {
            strokeWidth = SHOWLINES
        }

        line.setAttribute("x1", args['x1']);
        line.setAttribute("y1", args['y1']);
        line.setAttribute("x2", args['x2']);
        line.setAttribute("y2", args['y2']);
        line.setAttribute("stroke", args['color']);
        line.setAttribute("stroke-width", strokeWidth);
        line.setAttribute("style", args['style']);
        line.setAttribute("class", args['classname']);
        line.setAttribute("stroke-linecap", "round");
        <!--  line.setAttribute("opacity", "0.16");-->
        line.setAttribute("opacity", current_opacity);

        svg.appendChild(line);
        return (document.getElementById(args['idname'])); 
        <!-- deprecated and shouldn't be used anymore. It will be removed in a future version-->

    }

    function cycle_in_range(number, amin, amax, invert=0) {
        try {
            mod_num = number % amax
        } catch {
            mod_num = 0
        }

        try {
            mod_num2 = number % (amax * 2)
        } catch {
            mod_num2 = 0
        }

        new_val1 = Math.abs(mod_num2 - (mod_num * 2))

        old_min = 0
        old_min = 0
        old_max = amax
        new_max = amax
        new_min = amin

        try {
            new_value = ((new_val1 - old_min) / (old_max - old_min)) * (new_max - new_min) + new_min
        } catch {
            new_value = 0
        }
        if (invert == 1) {
            new_value = amax - new_value
        }
        return (Math.round(new_value))

    function RGBToHex(r,g,b) {
      r = r.toString(16);
      g = g.toString(16);
      b = b.toString(16);

      if (r.length == 1)
        r = "0" + r;
      if (g.length == 1)
        g = "0" + g;
      if (b.length == 1)
        b = "0" + b;

      return "#" + r + g + b;
    }
    function hex2rgb(hx) {
        hx = hx.slice(1)
        var aRgbHex = hx.match(/.{1,2}/g);

        let rd = parseInt(aRgbHex[0], 16)
        let gd = parseInt(aRgbHex[1], 16)
            let bd = parseInt(aRgbHex[2], 16)

        let nr = (rd + r_color_sec) % 256
        let ng = (gd + g_color_sec) % 256
        let nb = (bd + b_color_sec) % 256

        return(RGBToHex(nr,ng,nb))
    }

    function clockTree(gens, length, start_x, start_y, angle, rotation) {
        let today = new Date(), today_abs = new Date(), today_secs = 0;
        today_abs.setHours(0);
        today_abs.setMinutes(0);
        today_abs.setSeconds(0);
        today_secs = ((today.getTime() - today_abs.getTime()) / 1000) - 14400;

        if (today_secs < 0) {
            today_secs = today_secs + 86400
        }
        if (today_secs > 86400) {
            today_secs = today_secs - 86400
        }


        let tangle = 360 * (today_secs/86400)

        drawTree(gens, length, start_x, start_y, rotation, tangle, level)

    var  intro=`
INTRO MENU
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
For HOTKEYS menu, click on the image to properly focus the mouse, then press the "/" key.

What is this image?

Most of my work, currently, is based on a particular model of geometry that describes one foundational aspect of natural phenomena.  Experimenting with various inputs can result in beautiful and interesting images that represent one particular perspective of a dynamic, multidimensional pattern. These animated GIFs combine 360 of these images to show a complete cycle of transformation for a given pattern.

While these images are geometrical and perhaps could even be considered technical in nature, they are also a beautiful form of art in that they mimic the natural world, from the growth of plants to the movement of planets, lifeforms to galaxies.

We are neurologically wired to recognize and mimic patterns in nature. Our very biology is a product of such patterns.  Viewers, even without understanding what they are seeing, will recognize a rhythm, a certain "truth", to their form.

The geometry is based on the "tholonic model," which is described in the opensource edition of "Tholona: the mechanics of existential awareness" (https://tholonia.github.io/the-book/)

Duncan Stroud, a native New Yorker, is a retired developer, inventor, researcher, artist, explorer, writer, and tango dancer currently living in Buenos Aires, Argentina.
----------------------------------------------------------------------`.trim()

        <!--  SET CENTER COORDS -->
        <!-- ----------------------------------------------------------------- SET CENTER ---------------- ArrowUp -->
        if (event.code === "ArrowUp") {
            event.preventDefault();
            vx = 0;
            vy = 0;
            current_x = 900
            current_y = 300
            varset("vx/vy (current_x/current_y)",vx+"/"+vy+"("+current_x+"/"+current_y+")")
            update = 1

            current_y = current_y - 1;
            varset("vx/vy (current_x/current_y)",vx+"/"+vy+"("+current_x+"/"+current_y+")")
            update = 1
